values:
tomorrow i will be murdered by my graphics teacher.

please send all flowers to the hennessey-powell funeral home.

i was just gonna make a teenangst post, but sometimes even i have to remind myself that everything's gonna be just fine and work out somehow. tt always will, frustration is temporary. all hard feelings are.

i keep thinking about what i want for christmas and what to buy my family. i need more money cause i donno how i'm gonna top last year.

i never saw the first episode of sixfeetunder until the other day, so good that it's on tv again.

there's alot of junk to do tomorrow, agh.

i haven't talked to anyone online in forever.

today started out too cold and then got too warm.

after ignoring the oil light in my car for five days i finally got it checked. there was none, not to mention there was no antifreeze, hahaha. i need to take better care of her. i just realized i didn't name her yet.

i am drowning in english and graphics. so bad. i intend on resurfacing somehow, i always have. im doing real good in precal though, it might have something to do with me already taking it and ap calc.

ive been having(remembering) alot of dreams involving people ive barely ever talked to. alot of dreams in general, i wish i could remember them now.

i am a pizzaface now. i would say its stress but im never really stressed because im too busy relaxing(procrastinating). i cant stop touching my face.


everytime i die i mean write in this i get nostalgic then a zesty feeling for the future.

i got new tshirts after washing all my old ones with red sheets and turning them pink. 

after mowing the lawn and all its leaves in the humidity i got in the mood for fall. i like the three days that the weather is crisp but comfortable.

i wonna change my myspace headline but i never have so i feel like i can't. i think i'm gonna do it. 
my philosophy these days seems to be 'let go.' i have my memory and that's all that matters.

this is like walking up a down escalator but i can't help it.

help as an english work looks strange.
hahahahaha. the picture is three years old but i have hair in my face in all my others, naturally.

i'm liking college better than highschool, though i don't dig coming home at 5:30-6:30 some nights. so far i'm doing half-assed work but i'll get into the school mode someday.

time is starting to go by fast. there needs to be more days off. the thing about this summer is i have no five hundred dollar phone bill to show for it. i lost count of the time since we had a real conversation. i miss looking forward to eachother.

i just got my first credit card and i'm gonna blow money and create some good credit.

college tomorrow, and i'm not looking forward to commuting every day.
everyone seems real chill though.
i just got my scholarships for honors, so i've got 12k in scholarships now and tuition is around 10k total. so good.

yea i wasted my summer, but i waste all my time, so i don't mind.

i've been in the mood for thanksgiving for a couple of weeks now so hopefully that'll come quick.

i feel real weird not writing a vague entry.

i'm working this optimism thing though.


oh yea! steve irwin hahahahahahaha. idiot. that's all i have to say.

i'm gonna try my best to not take life half as seriously as i have been (cause it's so tired!).



(makes buzzer noise)
whenever there's something i want, by the time i get there it's over.

this icon is over two years old now and officially a classic.

thank you roseanne and deanna.

no idea why, but i feel optimistic.

there's a lot of junk going on with just about everyone in my life, but i still feel good.
it's ok to treat me bad i'm resilient right
i'm not down with being a jealous person. or a possessive one.

i went for my physical on monday and the new way they do tb is horrible.

i'm feelin' good but kinda lonely lately (forever).

this stawberry cheesecake icecream tastes like my childhood.
it reminds me of those waferlike sugarcones and cartons of neopolitan in my grandparents' kitchen.

so weirdd.

i think one day everyone's struggles will end and it'll be beautiful.
you won't realize it right away, just like when you get over being sick and you have that epiphany all like "hey, i'm better now"


"hey, life's better now"

i feel more anxious than usual.

i've been trying to think and put things in perspective but i feel like the blur you see when you look out from a carousel.

i'm tired of sleeping my problems away.

i feel like i od'd on myself.


i feel like i od'd on feeling.

i have all these thoughts all the time. but they just jumble and merge and block the exit.


i love when people spill their guts. there's nothing more human or relatable than someone at their worst or most candid, and i admire that.
i'm all for getting to know people better.


i need to work some things out.

i feel like a completely different person since last month.

more like i seem different to other people, but i'm still the same in my own head.


i wonder why i'm going into a math/science field when clearly i'm a history/literature person. this should be fun.

i just wish i got my school email address already cause i'm the onlyy one without a college facebook.


i think this song is gonna join my list of alltime favorites.


it's six am. sleep? no. watching bad morning tv waiting until it turns good but falling asleep before it does? hell yes.

i'm going craazy.

i feel completely alone without you, and i'll admit, i never thought i would.

i just want to expel my bloody lungs out of my body screaming
and there are a million reasons why.

i wish i could list them for you.
i wish i had someone to list them to.


i heard some of the best words today from someone, though.

since graduation i have been real lazy.
i've been sleeping for twelve hours straight each day.
i keep thinking of everything i'm gonna do instead of getting up and doing it.


i had a good time at a grad party the other day.
it's always the people you know least that you want to know most.
the word "friend" has become synonymous with "collectible" and that's not cool.
i press on in the constant social crusade.


you have been too busy for too long.
so little time, so much tuberculosis.

the computer lives.

i haven't felt healthy in over a month.

life feels vague while it's in this transition period and i can't wait until summer sets in.


i hate thinking what i'm thinking

there's nothing left to do but reformat my computer.
goodbye everything, besides pictures, important documents, and music. which is everything.

the proms were ill and i had ten times more fun than i thought i would. spent the four days with people i love, new and old.
andd i still have one coming up which will be equally bitchin.

my computer is ill.
thankfully the internet and aim work in safe mode somehow.

i still might not be online that often until this is fixed.


i really can't stand 800x600.

i feel like i should write, but then again i've been feeling a lot lately.
i've been all thoughts and i wish i was numb again.

i have one of those pimples that hide under your skin and turn the surrounding 3 acres red.

and i finally get the full meaning out of those night exchange explicit chat commercials!
don't lie to me, it makes me feel like shit.
I wish I actually talked to someone about my personal life.
With the changing seasons and all I feel like it's high time I change, too.

I've been inside my own head for so long.
I feel like I forgot how to communicate.


I'm almost done painting my room, but now I'm secondguessing the color.
I was going with red but now I think brown might be nice.

i want to drown myself in a bathtub.
not in that selfdestructive way,
but the act of drowning is synonymous with this feeling.

urgency, action.


it makes sense to me.

cold porcelain and the feeling of water up your nose isn't that beautiful.


i don't want weekend snow.

There should be snow if it's gonna be cold.
I could go for summer right now.


I've been so tired today.

I've been over school for a long time now.

I'd like to think I'd start updating more, but who knows.

All I know is that I could really go for bacon and eggs from the diner right now.

There are so many things I'd do that school/no income inhibits.

I got into the three colleges I applied to;
Tiiime to choose my life.


I need some change, things have been the same for too long.


Graduation in four months!

"How did you learn about NJIT and why are you applying for admission?"

does anyone know how long my answer to that should be? cause I could answer that in a sentence.

So I was pathetic a year ago; but that's everyone's thoughts every year!

More on this after my birthday.

Your Birthdate: January 7
You are an island. You don't need anyone else to make you happy. And though you see yourself as a loner, people are drawn to you. Deep and sensitive, you tend to impress others with your insights. You also tend to be psychic - so listen to that inner voice! Your strength: Your self sufficiency Your weakness: You despise authority Your power color: Maroon Your power symbol: Hammer Your power month: July
What Does Your Birth Date Mean?

I have given up on schoolwork 95%.

But there are good things and people to give hope !

I could go for it being the Tuesday night before Thanksgiving right about now.

I'll have you know that I filled out over half that survey until it deleted itself.


ps where are you forever

I hate our neighbors.
I try to pull into the driveway and idiots are standing there, so they WATCH me pull up to the curb.

I hope they all get avian flu and die so I can live in peace.

Money dictates everyone's lives.

I hate it.

Today my internet was inoperable for a long time.

Near death experience, but I solved it.

Round two tomorrow.

I just really want and need to sit around and do nothing.
I wish I didn't care enough to be overwhelmed by nothing and everything.

I just had a dream where I was at a place that was the pc auditorium/movietheatre/dancefloor and someone was all "hey look at the people having sex!" but I tried and all I saw were about six ghetto couples grinding among us. There were people standing on the floor but then they filtered out and only sophomores remained and started dancing like old couples before totally laying down next to eachother and not moving. For a moment I got caught up in the oldpeople dancing and somehow was able to dance with myself and was holding a mysterious back and hand but nothing else. We pointed out Sommer laying among the sophomores in a white hoodie with neon colors. Then I went home, but home was this giant house with a store that doubled as a garage attached and it was who else but the Camdens house. I still don't know how the church could afford to give them their huge house and make an addition on it. They weren't there anyway. Roseanne and I ended up playing hide and seek after we were playing around on some sort of street sweeping contraption. Then someone came in the shop and there was a strange woman at the register and i was stuck in some aisle by lindt truffles because it was two feet wide and I dropped a white chocolate one on the floor but couldn't reach it. Then when I was walking inside I was hiding from my sister, not Roseanne anymore. I tried hiding in her room and then hid in the tub in our bathroom until she came to the stairs and said something that apparently ended the game.

I am tired but I had to share.
Guess who else was bored. Not to mention I needed an update.

god bless my dislocating knees.
need summer books and more.
room is hiroshima.
greater separation.

i just got out of bed. what the fuck.

i don't think my bank account of 32.91 has changed in the past eight years.
yea, i'm saving for a vacation getaway.

haaaahahaha.

my eyes burn and my hair hurts.
